    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 27-SI SERIES, TYPE 200 - REPAIR PROCEDURES - DIODE TRIO CHECK</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DIODE TRIO CHECK</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the diode from the end frame assembly by detaching the nuts and attaching screw
                <hotlnk document="s08015_7.xml" xrefid="f0801508">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect an ohmmeter having a 1-1/2 volt cell, and a lower range scale (R x 1 or R x 10).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach the meter leads to the single connector and to one of the three connectors
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801509">Figure 9</hotlnk>). Observe the reading.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801509" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801509" filename="../figg08/G0801509.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Diode Trio Check</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. OHMMETER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SINGLE CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. THREE CONNECTORS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reverse the ohmmeter leads to the same two connectors. If both readings are the same,
                replace the diode trio. A good diode trio will give one high and one low reading.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat this same test between the single connector and each of the other two connectors.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The diode trios differing in appearance may be specified for use. The two are completely
                        interchangeable.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
